The paper deals with the problem of inferring the probability distribution associated with a language, given data consisting of an infinite sequence of elements of the language. This involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also uses the theory of Kolmogorov complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the associated predictions, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
